Your repository clearly contains things like:
	•	command_schema.json
	•	commands/
	•	command structures referenced by Copilot

That means actions in the system are not random API calls. They are formal commands.

Conceptually:
COMMAND
actor
authority
action
parameters
timestamp
Example: json: {
  "command": "create_vehicle_offer",
  "domain": "CARSHUNTER",
  "actor": "dealer_17",
  "parameters": {
    "vehicle": "Range Rover Evoque",
    "price": 54000
  }
}
This is important because it creates structured governance actions.

Most software skips this layer.
